<item>
            <title>[QPID-3108] QueueSender incorrectly checks for null queue</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-3108</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JMS documents that you can create a QueueSender with a null queue (called an unidentified queue in the documentation) and this is fine as long as you don&apos;t try to use one fo the send methods that relies on the queue being set up at construction time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current code checks for null queue in the getters too and so causes erroneous UnsupportedOperationException exceptions to be throw when they are used with an unidentified queue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
